    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-06T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="127"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1012: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative of the President</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-06T20:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 6, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>33. In the conference held this afternoon with the Nicaraguan delegates they
                    declared their readiness to sign a protocol incorporating the points agreed on
                    up to the present time and with respect to the elimination of point No. 6,
                    referred to in my telegram No. 32, of today. They stated the retention or
                    elimination of this point referring to stamps would not alter their willingness
                    to sign.</p>
                <p>If this point does not cause delay the protocol is likely to be signed within a
                    few days. The matter of a permanent secretariat is now under discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
